text: The 14th Olonets Infantry Regiment was an infantry regiment of the Russian Empire's Imperial Russian Army. It took part in wars against the Ottoman Empire and the First French Empire (1813–1814), as well as conflicts in Poland (1831 and 1863), Hungary (1849) and the Crimea. == References == * * * Category:Infantry regiments of the Russian Empire Category:Łomża Governorate Category:Military units and formations established in 1798 Category:Military units and formations disestablished in 1918
title: 14th Olonets Infantry Regiment
